cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with improving the accuracy of visual odometry using computer vision techniques, specifically stereo visual odometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with robotic vehicles, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for sun estimation suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of absolute orientation information, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with outdoor driving, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics).
